trans-unit.source: Application Insights for JavaScript web apps | Microsoft Azure
trans-unit.target: Application Insights for JavaScript web apps | Microsoft Azure

trans-unit.source: Get page view and session counts, web client data, and track usage patterns. Detect exceptions and performance issues in JavaScript web pages.
trans-unit.target: Get page view and session counts, web client data, and track usage patterns. Detect exceptions and performance issues in JavaScript web pages.

trans-unit.source: Find out about the performance and usage of your web page.
trans-unit.target: Find out about the performance and usage of your web page.

trans-unit.source: Add Visual Studio Application Insights to your page, and you'll find out how many users you have, how often they come back, and which pages they use most.
trans-unit.target: Add Visual Studio Application Insights to your page, and you'll find out how many users you have, how often they come back, and which pages they use most.

trans-unit.source: You'll also get reports of load times and any exceptions.
trans-unit.target: You'll also get reports of load times and any exceptions.

trans-unit.source: Add a few <linkText>custom events and metrics[track]</linkText><title></title>, and you can analyze in detail the most popular features, the most common mistakes, and tune your page to success with your users.
trans-unit.target: Add a few <linkText>custom events and metrics[track]</linkText><title></title>, and you can analyze in detail the most popular features, the most common mistakes, and tune your page to success with your users.

trans-unit.source: <linkText>Choose New, Developer Services, Application Insights.</linkText>
trans-unit.target: <linkText>Choose New, Developer Services, Application Insights.</linkText>

trans-unit.source: If you already set up server telemetry for your <linkText>ASP.NET[greenbrown]</linkText><title></title> or <linkText>Java[java]</linkText><title></title> web app, you'll get the picture from both client and server angles.
trans-unit.target: If you already set up server telemetry for your <linkText>ASP.NET[greenbrown]</linkText><title></title> or <linkText>Java[java]</linkText><title></title> web app, you'll get the picture from both client and server angles.

trans-unit.source: The two streams will be integrated in the Application Insights portal.
trans-unit.target: The two streams will be integrated in the Application Insights portal.

trans-unit.source: If you don't have an Azure subscription and would like to try Application Insights on your web page, visit <linkText>Try Application Insights</linkText><title></title>.
trans-unit.target: If you don't have an Azure subscription and would like to try Application Insights on your web page, visit <linkText>Try Application Insights</linkText><title></title>.

trans-unit.source: The Application Insights resource is where data about your page's performance and usage is displayed.
trans-unit.target: The Application Insights resource is where data about your page's performance and usage is displayed.

trans-unit.source: (If you already created a resource, maybe to collect data from your web server, skip this step.)
trans-unit.target: (If you already created a resource, maybe to collect data from your web server, skip this step.)

trans-unit.source: In the <linkText>Azure portal</linkText><title></title>, create a new Application Insights resource:
trans-unit.target: In the <linkText>Azure portal</linkText><title></title>, create a new Application Insights resource:

trans-unit.source: <linkText>Choose New, Developer Services, Application Insights.</linkText>
trans-unit.target: <linkText>Choose New, Developer Services, Application Insights.</linkText>

trans-unit.source: Questions already? More about creating a resource[new].
trans-unit.target: Questions already? More about creating a resource[new].

trans-unit.source: In Quick Start, get the script for web pages:
trans-unit.target: In Quick Start, get the script for web pages:

trans-unit.source: ![On your app overview blade, choose Quick Start, Get code to monitor my web pages.
trans-unit.target: ![On your app overview blade, choose Quick Start, Get code to monitor my web pages.

trans-unit.source: Copy the script.](./media/app-insights-javascript/02-monitor-web-page.png)
trans-unit.target: Copy the script.](./media/app-insights-javascript/02-monitor-web-page.png)

trans-unit.source: Insert the script just before the </head> tag of every page you want to track.
trans-unit.target: Insert the script just before the </head> tag of every page you want to track.

trans-unit.source: If your website has a master page, you can put the script there.
trans-unit.target: If your website has a master page, you can put the script there.

trans-unit.source: For example:
trans-unit.target: For example:

trans-unit.source: In an ASP.NET MVC project, you'd put it in View\Shared\\_Layout.cshtml
trans-unit.target: In an ASP.NET MVC project, you'd put it in View\Shared\\_Layout.cshtml

trans-unit.source: In a SharePoint site, on the control panel, open <linkText>Site Settings / Master Page</linkText><title></title>.
trans-unit.target: In a SharePoint site, on the control panel, open <linkText>Site Settings / Master Page</linkText><title></title>.

trans-unit.source: The script contains the instrumentation key that directs the data to your Application Insights resource.
trans-unit.target: The script contains the instrumentation key that directs the data to your Application Insights resource.

trans-unit.source: *(If you're using a well-known web page framework, look around for Application Insights adaptors.
trans-unit.target: *(If you're using a well-known web page framework, look around for Application Insights adaptors.

trans-unit.source: For example, there's <linkText>an AngularJS module</linkText><title></title>.)*
trans-unit.target: For example, there's <linkText>an AngularJS module</linkText><title></title>.)*

trans-unit.source: Run your web app, use it a while to generate telemetry, and wait a few seconds.
trans-unit.target: Run your web app, use it a while to generate telemetry, and wait a few seconds.

trans-unit.source: You can either run it using the F5 key on your development machine, or publish it and let users play with it.
trans-unit.target: You can either run it using the F5 key on your development machine, or publish it and let users play with it.

trans-unit.source: If you want to check the telemetry that a web app is sending to Application Insights, use your browser's debugging tools (F12 on many browsers).
trans-unit.target: If you want to check the telemetry that a web app is sending to Application Insights, use your browser's debugging tools (F12 on many browsers).

trans-unit.source: Data is sent to dc.services.visualstudio.com.
trans-unit.target: Data is sent to dc.services.visualstudio.com.

trans-unit.source: In the application overview blade, there's a chart near the top that shows average time to load pages into the browser:
trans-unit.target: In the application overview blade, there's a chart near the top that shows average time to load pages into the browser:

trans-unit.source: *No data yet?
trans-unit.target: *No data yet?

trans-unit.source: Click Refresh at the top of the page.
trans-unit.target: Click Refresh at the top of the page.

trans-unit.source: Still nothing?
trans-unit.target: Still nothing?

trans-unit.source: See <linkText>Troubleshooting[qna]</linkText><title></title>.*
trans-unit.target: See <linkText>Troubleshooting[qna]</linkText><title></title>.*

trans-unit.source: Click that chart, and you get a more detailed version:
trans-unit.target: Click that chart, and you get a more detailed version:

trans-unit.source: This is a stacked chart which breaks the total page load time into the <linkText>standard timings defined by W3C</linkText><title></title>.
trans-unit.target: This is a stacked chart which breaks the total page load time into the <linkText>standard timings defined by W3C</linkText><title></title>.

trans-unit.source: Note that the network connect time is usually lower than you might expect, because it's an average over all requests from the browser to the server.
trans-unit.target: Note that the network connect time is usually lower than you might expect, because it's an average over all requests from the browser to the server.

trans-unit.source: Many individual requests have a connect time of 0 because there is already an active connection to the server.
trans-unit.target: Many individual requests have a connect time of 0 because there is already an active connection to the server.

trans-unit.source: Further down in the details blade, there's a grid segmented by page URL:
trans-unit.target: Further down in the details blade, there's a grid segmented by page URL:

trans-unit.source: If you'd like to see the performance of the pages over time, double-click the grid and change its chart type:
trans-unit.target: If you'd like to see the performance of the pages over time, double-click the grid and change its chart type:

trans-unit.source: Back on the overview blade, click Usage:
trans-unit.target: Back on the overview blade, click Usage:

trans-unit.source: Users: The count of distinct users over the time range of the chart.
trans-unit.target: Users: The count of distinct users over the time range of the chart.

trans-unit.source: (Cookies are used to identify returning users.)
trans-unit.target: (Cookies are used to identify returning users.)

trans-unit.source: Sessions: A session is counted when a user has not made any requests for 30 minutes.
trans-unit.target: Sessions: A session is counted when a user has not made any requests for 30 minutes.

trans-unit.source: Page views Counts the number of calls to trackPageView(), typically called once in each web page.
trans-unit.target: Page views Counts the number of calls to trackPageView(), typically called once in each web page.

trans-unit.source: Click any of the charts to see more detail.
trans-unit.target: Click any of the charts to see more detail.

trans-unit.source: Notice that you can change the time range of the charts.
trans-unit.target: Notice that you can change the time range of the charts.

trans-unit.source: Click a chart to see other metrics that you can display, or add a new chart and select the metrics it displays.
trans-unit.target: Click a chart to see other metrics that you can display, or add a new chart and select the metrics it displays.

trans-unit.source: Metrics can only be displayed in some combinations.
trans-unit.target: Metrics can only be displayed in some combinations.

trans-unit.source: When you select a metric, the incompatible ones are disabled.
trans-unit.target: When you select a metric, the incompatible ones are disabled.

trans-unit.source: By default, a page count occurs each time a new page loads into the client browser.
trans-unit.target: By default, a page count occurs each time a new page loads into the client browser.

trans-unit.source: But you might want to count additional page views.
trans-unit.target: But you might want to count additional page views.

trans-unit.source: For example, a page might display its content in tabs and you want to count a page when the user switches tabs.
trans-unit.target: For example, a page might display its content in tabs and you want to count a page when the user switches tabs.

trans-unit.source: Or JavaScript code in the page might load new content without changing the browser's URL.
trans-unit.target: Or JavaScript code in the page might load new content without changing the browser's URL.

trans-unit.source: Insert a JavaScript call like this at the appropriate point in your client code:
trans-unit.target: Insert a JavaScript call like this at the appropriate point in your client code:

trans-unit.source: The page name can contain the same characters as a URL, but anything after "#" or "?" will be ignored.
trans-unit.target: The page name can contain the same characters as a URL, but anything after "#" or "?" will be ignored.

trans-unit.source: Usually page view telemetry is analyzed by Application Insights and you see only cumulative reports, averaged over all your users.
trans-unit.target: Usually page view telemetry is analyzed by Application Insights and you see only cumulative reports, averaged over all your users.

trans-unit.source: But for debugging purposes, you can also look at individual page view events.
trans-unit.target: But for debugging purposes, you can also look at individual page view events.

trans-unit.source: In the Diagnostic Search blade, set Filters to Page View.
trans-unit.target: In the Diagnostic Search blade, set Filters to Page View.

trans-unit.source: Select any event to see more detail.
trans-unit.target: Select any event to see more detail.

trans-unit.source: In the details page, click "..." to see even more detail.
trans-unit.target: In the details page, click "..." to see even more detail.

trans-unit.source: If you use <linkText>Search[diagnostic]</linkText><title></title>, notice that you have to match whole words: "Abou" and "bout" do not match "About", but "Abou* " does.
trans-unit.target: If you use <linkText>Search[diagnostic]</linkText><title></title>, notice that you have to match whole words: "Abou" and "bout" do not match "About", but "Abou* " does.

trans-unit.source: And you cannot begin a search term with a wildcard.
trans-unit.target: And you cannot begin a search term with a wildcard.

trans-unit.source: For example, searching for "*bou" would not match "About".
trans-unit.target: For example, searching for "*bou" would not match "About".

trans-unit.source: <linkText>Learn more about diagnostic search[diagnostic]</linkText><title></title>
trans-unit.target: <linkText>Learn more about diagnostic search[diagnostic]</linkText><title></title>

trans-unit.source: Page view duration—The time it takes to load the page and start running scripts.
trans-unit.target: Page view duration—The time it takes to load the page and start running scripts.

trans-unit.source: Specifically, the interval between starting to load the page and execution of the trackPageView.
trans-unit.target: Specifically, the interval between starting to load the page and execution of the trackPageView.

trans-unit.source: If you moved trackPageView from its usual position after the initialization of the script, it will reflect a different value.
trans-unit.target: If you moved trackPageView from its usual position after the initialization of the script, it will reflect a different value.

trans-unit.source: Want to find out what your users do with your app?
trans-unit.target: Want to find out what your users do with your app?

trans-unit.source: By inserting calls in your client and server code, you can send your own telemetry to Application Insights.
trans-unit.target: By inserting calls in your client and server code, you can send your own telemetry to Application Insights.

trans-unit.source: For example, you can find out the numbers of users who create orders without completing them, or which validation errors are hit most often, or the average score in a game.
trans-unit.target: For example, you can find out the numbers of users who create orders without completing them, or which validation errors are hit most often, or the average score in a game.
